==English==

===Adjective===
====Pronunciation====
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /p3`fIkt/
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /pɝfɪkt/

'''perfect'''
# Fitting its definition [[precise]]ly, as, a ''perfect'' circle
# Having all of its parts in harmony with a common purpose
:Ex. That bucket with the hole in the bottom is a poor bucket, but it is perfect for watering plants.
# (''Grammar'': of a tense or verb form) Representing a completed action.  See [[present perfect]], [[past perfect]] ([[pluperfect]]), and [[future perfect]], and contrast with [[imperfect]].  See also [[perfective]] and [[imperfective]].

